    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      282.15,
      543.73,
      296.15
    ],
    "text": "1991(2) SLR 206 that \u201cRelief will not be granted for default in prosecuting an",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      303.27,
      157.22,
      317.27
    ],
    "text": "appeal where;",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      324.39,
      543.94,
      338.39
    ],
    "text": "(a) the default has resulted from the negligence of the client or both the client",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      345.63,
      217.25,
      359.63
    ],
    "text": "and his attorney-at-law;",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      366.75,
      543.94,
      380.75
    ],
    "text": "(b) the default has resulted from the negligence of the attorney-at-law in which",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      387.87,
      543.91,
      401.87
    ],
    "text": "event the principle is that the negligence of the attorney-at-law is the negligence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      409.01,
      340.63,
      423.01
    ],
    "text": "of the client and the client must suffer for it.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      430.13,
      543.93,
      444.13
    ],
    "text": "As the applicant's default appeared to be the result of his own negligence as well",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      451.25,
      543.93,
      465.25
    ],
    "text": "as the negligence of his attorney-at-law, the conduct of the appellant and his",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      472.37,
      543.91,
      486.37
    ],
    "text": "attorney-at-law cannot be excused. The appellant had failed to adduce sufficient",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      493.49,
      291.89,
      507.49
    ],
